cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use cue in research or write about it, please cite this entry."
title: "cue: an agent profile manager and skill package manager for Claude Code, Codex, and 8 other AI coding agents"
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "Viktor"
    family-names: "Nagy"
    alias: "NagyVikt"
    website: "https://github.com/NagyVikt"
abstract: >-
  cue is an open-source CLI that scopes AI agent skills, MCP servers, plugins,
  rules, commands, hooks, persona, playbooks, quality gates, and structural
  evals per-directory across 10 AI coding agents (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex,
  Cursor, Cline, Google Gemini CLI, GitHub Copilot, Windsurf, Roo Code,
  Sourcegraph Amp, Aider). cue introduces a 5-dimension expert-agent profile
  model (persona, playbooks, quality gates, evals, failure loop) that treats
  agent expertise as a composable system rather than a static toolbox.
  It includes a GitHub Code Search-powered skill-discovery engine, a per-OS
  system CLI dependency installer, an outbound PR flow with throttle and
  opt-out controls, an LLM-drafted failure-feedback loop, and JSON-LD
  Schema.org generation for AI search engine citation.
keywords:
  - claude-code
  - codex
  - cursor
  - cline
  - gemini-cli
  - github-copilot
  - ai-coding-agent
  - mcp
  - model-context-protocol
  - skill-management
  - agent-profile-manager
  - prompt-engineering
  - token-optimization
  - llm-tooling
